{
  "target": "Validate",
  "kind": "model_estimation",
  "source": "BestFit v2.0.0 (c2e6192), transcribed from the new Test_Validate_IrregularTimeSeries_ReturnsFalse tests in src/RMC.BestFit.Tests/TimeSeriesModels/{AutoRegressive,MovingAverage,ARIMA,ARIMAX}Tests.cs, and reproduced against the real Numerics/RMC.BestFit libraries by tools/oracle_emitter's Validate target (Task 21). All four TimeSeries families gained a Validate guard that rejects TimeInterval.Irregular: the ARMA recursion, the differencing operator and the Fourier seasonality term all index by regular position, so an irregular series must be resampled before estimating. Structural check only: validation_message_contains is a substring probe, not a byte-exact pin of the message text (the C++ message is hand-verified against the C# source in the model headers). The trailing *_regular_interval_control cases hold the identical data on a regular interval and assert is_valid=1, so the guard is discriminating within the fixture itself. Both builders construct an Irregular series ordinate-by-ordinate (the (interval, start, values) constructor rejects Irregular in C# exactly as in the port); the index spacing is inert because every TimeSeries family indexes by position.",
